			<ns0:name>mmorten...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100268164290167392978/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;What version of the SDK are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
   0.4
&lt;b&gt;What version of the runtime are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
   NaCl rev 5524
&lt;b&gt;On what operating system?&lt;/b&gt;
   Windows
&lt;b&gt;What browser are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
   13.0.782.10 (87958)

&lt;b&gt;Please include version information for both the OS and the browser.&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;What steps will reproduce the problem?&lt;/b&gt;
1. Launch chrome with --enable-nacl-debug --no-sandbox
2. Make sure you have a server running to load nexes
3. Navigate to a page that contains an untrusted nexe

&lt;b&gt;What is the expected output? What do you see instead?&lt;/b&gt;

The nexe should halt until the debugger (i.e. gdb from a Linux machine) sends a continue command.  It does not, even though the debug port (4014) gets opened.  Instead, the nexe loads and runs.



